The Ebonyi State government has thanked President Muhammadu Buhari for his two-day official working visit to the state. Governor David Umahi yesterday expressed ‘deep gratitude’ over the visit.   Patients, relatives lament rejection at hospital     Cross River APC: governorship aspirants reject consensus…     Dagogo accuses Rivers police boss of bias   President Buhari, on May 5 and 6, visited the state and inaugurated some projects, including King David University of Medical Science and Technology, the University Flyover, dualised concrete road, and Presidential Lounge of the International Airport. Umahi, who described Buhari’s presence as ‘generous’, said: “We are pleased to convey to you the warm appreciation of Ebonyi people and the Southeast, over your positive dispositions to the development of the zone. “While we assure your Excellency of our unwavering support and solidarity, please accept always, the assurances of the esteemed regards and best wishes of the government and Ebonyi people.”